    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-10-05T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-10-05T19:00:00-05:00" n="1126"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1126">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-10-05T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 5, 1916, 7 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3899. Department’s instruction 3917, July 17.<note n="3" xml:id="d1126fn3">Not
                        printed.</note> Department would be glad to have a confidential report from
                        <persName corresp="#p_HHC1">Hoover</persName> as to the recent deportations
                    of civilians from Lille, Roubaix, and Tourcoing; also as to deportations from
                    Belgium, if any, and the present situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
